# str-mcp-purview configuration
#
# Delegated (signed-in admin) authentication. The server acts as the admin who
# signs in, so all actions respect that admin's Microsoft Purview RBAC.

# --- Microsoft Graph (sensitivity label tools) ---
# A Microsoft Entra "public client / native" app registration in your tenant,
# granted the DELEGATED permission: InformationProtectionPolicy.Read
# (with admin consent). Add redirect URI http://localhost for interactive login.
AZURE_TENANT_ID=your-tenant-id-or-domain
AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-public-client-app-id

# Optional: "interactive" (default, opens a browser) or "devicecode" (headless).
# PURVIEW_AUTH_MODE=interactive
# Optional: override the interactive redirect URI (must match the app reg).
# AZURE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost

# --- Security & Compliance PowerShell (DLP tools) ---
# Requires the ExchangeOnlineManagement module:
#   Install-Module ExchangeOnlineManagement -Scope CurrentUser
# On first DLP tool use the server runs Connect-IPPSSession, which opens an
# interactive sign-in. Optionally pre-fill the admin UPN to skip the picker:
# PURVIEW_UPN=admin@contoso.onmicrosoft.com
# Optional: path/name of the PowerShell 7+ executable (default: pwsh).
# PURVIEW_PWSH=pwsh
